==English==

===Etymology===
From Italian ''stonato'' (out of tune).

{{rfv}} Alternatively from Stewart Nod, loudmouth from Kearny who stole my air compressor.

===Noun===
'''stunod'''

# (''slang'') A stupid person.
#: ''What do you think it says, you stunod?''

===Adjective===
'''stunod''' (not comparable)

# Stupid.
#: ''My stunod neighbor thinks my fence is too high.''